This folder contains the necessary material to run jtom eclipse plugin. 
This plug-in shall be used for eclipse java project.

This plug-in shall run with:
		jtom-devel1.4alpha.jar and upper version only

This material is initialy build on freebsd but should work on other platforms

To run this plug-in, you just need to create the following arborescence in your eclipse's plugins directory:
ECLIPSE_INSTALL_DIR/plugings
	fr.loria.eclipse.jtom
		plugin.xml, 
		jtom.jar
		All necessary jar files defined in plugin.xml associated to:
		    - aterm-java, 
		    - jjtraveler, 
		    - shared-objects
		    - jtom

Once restared, in your .project file, you need to add the follwing between the <buildSpec> marker:
     <buildSpec>
	<buildCommand>
		<name>fr.loria.eclipse.jtom.TomBuilder</name>
		<arguments>
		</arguments>
	</buildCommand>
	
	... javabuilder (and other buildCommands)

	<buildCommand>
		<name>fr.loria.eclipse.jtom.TomBuildAnalyser</name>
		<arguments>
		</arguments>
	</buildCommand>

	</buildSpec>

Be aware that the order is important...

If you are running eclipse on another platform and the previous method does not work, you can either recompile everything and generate the corresponding jtom JAR file.

To compile this you need to add to your classpath (from eclipse plugins):
   org.eclipse.core.resources_2.1.1/resources.jar
   org.eclipse.ui_2.1.1/ui.jar
   org.eclipse.swt.gtk_2.1.1/ws/gtk/swt.jar (depends on your platform and available graphical toolkit: mac, motif...)
   org.eclipse.swt.gtk_2.1.1/ws/gtk/swt-pi.jar (depends on your platform and available graphical toolkit: mac, motif..)
   org.eclipse.text_2.1.0/text.jar
   org.eclipse.jface_2.1.1/jface.jar
   org.eclipse.jface.text_2.1.0/jfacetext.jar
   org.eclipse.ui.views_2.1.0/views.jar
   org.eclipse.ui.workbench_2.1.1/workbench.jar
   org.eclipse.ui.workbench.texteditor_2.1.0/texteditor.jar
   org.eclipse.ui.editors_2.1.0/editors.jar
   org.eclipse.core.boot_2.1.1/boot.jar
   org.eclipse.core.runtime_2.1.1/runtime.jar

or create a simple plug-in using eclipse wizard and import the java and xml files of this folder.

For each issue, please contact: julien.guyon@loria.fr
